Syntax: nmap <flag> <Target IP>

Basic Flags Used:

-sP -Scans the entire subnetwroks in an IP
-O -Provide with the details of OS within an specific IP
-A - Does an aggressive scan
-sT -Obtain Normal TCP connect through SYN/ACK
-sS -Sthealth scan which doesnt fully connect the Target  through TCP.

Example: sudo nmap -sS -A <IP> -Gives the open port and vulnarability in it.
